balcony /ˈbælkənɪ/

(balconies) 

1. N-COUNT A balcony is a platform on the outside of a building, above ground level, with a wall or railing around it. 阳台 

2. N-SING The balcony in a theatre or cinema is an area of seats above the main seating area. (戏院或电影院里的) 楼座

